Prompt 1: Adding Tess4J Dependency

Prompt:

Why am I getting “Cannot resolve symbol Tesseract” in my Spring Boot project?

AI Response Summary:
The AI explained that the error occurs when the Tess4J dependency is missing from pom.xml. It provided the correct Maven dependency:

<dependency>
    <groupId>net.sourceforge.tess4j</groupId>
    <artifactId>tess4j</artifactId>
    <version>5.11.0</version>
</dependency>


It also advised reloading the Maven project after adding the dependency.

Evaluation:
This response directly solved the issue. The explanation was technically correct and helped me understand the importance of dependency management in Maven projects.

Prompt 2: Fixing 404 Error in Spring Boot

Prompt:

I am getting a 404 error when testing /ocr/scan in Postman. Why?

AI Response Summary:
The AI explained that a 404 error may occur due to:

Incorrect URL path

Using GET instead of POST

Missing @RestController annotation

Controller not inside the base package

Application not restarted

It also clarified that browsers send GET requests by default, while the endpoint was defined using @PostMapping.

Evaluation:
This explanation helped distinguish between HTTP method issues and mapping errors. It reinforced understanding of how Spring Boot routing works.

Prompt 3: Testing File Upload in Postman

Prompt:

How do I upload an image file in Postman to test my OCR API?

AI Response Summary:
The AI provided step-by-step instructions:

Select POST method

Go to Body → form-data

Add key file

Change type from Text to File

Select image file (JPG/PNG)

It emphasized that the key name must match @RequestParam("file").

Evaluation:
This was extremely helpful because file upload configuration in Postman can be confusing. The instructions were accurate and resolved the issue immediately.

Prompt 4: Choosing Between PDF and Image Input

Prompt:

Should I upload an image or a PDF file for OCR testing?

AI Response Summary:
The AI explained that Tesseract works natively with images (JPG, PNG, TIFF).
PDFs require additional processing (PDF to image conversion) before OCR can be applied.
It recommended using images for the minimal working version.

Evaluation:
The explanation clarified scope boundaries and prevented unnecessary complexity. It also helped define the supported file types in the README documentation.
